divs: Sighting DetailsOn the night of Nov. 15th, 1973, four objects were sited off the coast of Florida from the West Palm Beach, Jai Lai Fronton. Stacked at a 45 deg angle in relation to each other, they were observed by hundreds of people looking out in a easterly direction. Then the lowest one in the pattern did a sudden 90 deg dive from its trajectory, straight down at a unbelievable speed. Then the 2nd one in the pattern did a similar dive into the same area. Same for the 3rd and 4th objects in this group. I know there are no manmade objects that could fly at that speed ...and maintain the speed thru a 90 deg turn and power dive to the deck (ocean surface). Missiles don't even move that fast.
Summary: 4 objects off of West Palm Beach, Fl. 1973.
